Cape Town is preparing for more heavy rains and possible flooding. Several areas were left without power yesterday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The City of Cape Town is on standby and ready after flooding caused havoc in several areas. The overnight flooding brought power outages, damages to infrastructure and road closures. More rain is expected on Saturday evening but the city says it's prepared. WATCH: More flooding expected in Cape Town “Every department in the City of Cape Town has its own contingency plans, its own disaster management plans and so departments have crews on standby,” said Sam Freeman of the Cape Town Disaster Risk Management. Heavy rains are forecast for Sunday afternoon and will most likely last until Monday. The city has appealed to residents to not dump rubbish in the drains. 